<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,806,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sipman &amp; Aptroot) Kantvilas" authorityName="Kantvilas" baseAuthorityName="Sipman &amp; Aptroot" box="[291,1279,846,868]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subForm" species="applanata" subForm="globulispora">
<emphasis box="[291,492,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Lambiella applanata</emphasis>
(Kantvilas &amp; Coppins) Kantvilas, 
<emphasis box="[830,979,846,868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">L. globulispora</emphasis>
(Sipman &amp; Aptroot) Kantvilas
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kantvilas &amp; Coppins) Kantvilas" authorityName="Kantvilas" baseAuthorityName="Kantvilas &amp; Coppins" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="umbratilis">
<emphasis box="[1327,1452,846,868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">L. umbratilis</emphasis>
(Kantvilas &amp; Coppins) Kantvilas
</taxonomicName>
with respect to the thin, grey thallus and prominent black prothallus, but differing from these by the absence of lobaric acid, the minute apothecia, 
<quantity box="[634,786,918,940]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.75" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="0.1025" valueMax="0.13" valueMin="0.075">0.075−0.13 mm</quantity>
wide, and subglobose to ellipsoid ascospores, 4–8.5 × 3–5 µm.
</paragraph>
